 2024 from the Department of Astronomy &amp;                Astrophysics at the University of California, Santa Cruz working                with Enrico Ramirez-Ruiz. I am interested in high-energy                astrophysics and fluid dynamics in interacting stellar binaries,                specifically those undergoing common envelope evolution. I                completed a BS Physics at the University of Colorado Denver in                2017 after earning a BA Theatre from Meredith College and                touring nationally as a musician and performing artist for                nearly a decade. </p>              <p> My non-research interests include bridging science and                society, equitable and inclusive STEM, and science advocacy and                policy. Personal interests include contemporary/aerial dance and                performing arts, creative vegetarian cuisine, cultivating                mindfulness, and spending quality time with my family. </p>              <a href="javascript:ReverseDisplay('uniquename')" class="button">Contact</a>              <br>              <br>              <div id="uniquename" style="display:none;">                <p><b>Email: <br>                    reverson (at) unc (dot) edu</b><br>                  <br>                  Mail: <br>                  R.W. Everson<br>                  UNC Physics &amp; Astronomy<br>                  120 E. Cameron Ave.<br>                  Phillips Hall CB3255 Chapel Hill, NC 27599</p>              </div>            </div>          </div>        </div>      </section>    </div>    <!-- Footer -->    <footer id="footer">      <div class="copyright">        <ul class="icons">          <li><a href="http://www.linkedin.com/in/rosaeverson" class="icon fa-linkedin">              <span class="label">LinkedIn</span></a></li>          <!--    <li><a href="http://www.facebook.com/rosawallaceeverson" class="icon fa-facebook">              <span cla